				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Chlorinated hydrocarbons are organic molecules characterized by the presence of at least one chlorine atom bonded to a carbon atom. They are widely used industrial solvents and degreasing agents. They have a wide range of uses, from making cookware to creating industrial solvents. They are environmentally persistent and have contaminated the environment through leakage in storage tanks and irresponsible disposal practices.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氯化碳氢化合物是一种有机分子，其特点是碳原子上至少含有一个氯原子。它们是广泛使用的工业溶剂和脱脂剂。它们用途广泛，从制造炊具到制造工业溶剂。它们对环境具有持久性，并因储罐泄漏和不负责任的处置做法而污染环境。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Variable, contains at least one Cl-C bond</sumFormula>
